com.thinkaurelius.titan.core
Interface TitanKey

All Superinterfaces:
com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Element, TitanElement, TitanType, TitanVertex, com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Vertex
public interface TitanKey
extends TitanType

TitanKey is an extension of TitanType for properties.

In addition to TitanType, TitanKey defines:

  • Data Type: The accepted types of attribute values.
  • Index: Whether attribute values are indexed. If a property key is configured to be indexed, then all properties with that key are indexed which means one can retrieve vertices for that key and a value via TitanTransaction.getVertices(TitanKey, Object)
  • Uniqueness: When a TitanKey is configured to be unique it is ensured that at most one vertex can be associated with a particular value for that key. As an example, social security number is a unique property, since each SSN is associated with only one individual.

Author:
Matthias Bröcheler (me@matthiasb.com)

isUnique

boolean isUnique()
Checks whether this property key is unique. A property key is unique if all attributes for properties of this key are uniquely associated with the property's vertex. In other words, there is a functional mapping from attribute values to vertices.

Returns:
true, if this property key is unique, else false.
